title: Kim Kardashian Breaks Her Silence About That Alleged Second Sex Tape
text:
Kim Kardashian Breaks Her Silence About That Alleged Second Sex Tape Nicole Fabian-Weber 
Jawad Elatab/Splash News 
Settle down, everyone. Kim Kardashian does not have another sex tape . Not long after "scenes from a new Kim Kardashian sex tape" were released online, Kim broke he silence regarding the racy video. Spoiler alert: It's old news. 
Images of a woman who appears to be Kim in a skimpy bra were posted online earlier this week. In the scenes, the woman appears to be showing off her cleavage to a man holding a camera. Not surprisingly, shortly after the images were released, the world collectively rubbed their hands in anticipation of a never-before-seen Kim sex tape. But that's not the case. The images are just never-before-seen moments from her sex tape with Ray J. Aren't we over this already? 
More from CafeMom: Kim Kardashian's Butt Through the Years: An Evolution in Photos 
After the scenes were released, Kim and her reps quickly denied it being new. "Itâ€™s not new -- it's the same old sex tape," a spokesperson for Kim told the Daily Mail . 
Despite the fact that her sex tape skyrocketed her to worldwide fame, Kim has said on numerous occasions that she regrets her decision to distribute it. "If I do have one regret in life, that's it," the Selfish author told Love magazine last year. And before that, in a sit down interview with Oprah, Kim also said of the sex tape, "I felt like I really had to work 10 times harder to get people to see the real me." 
Needless to say, Kim probably isn't thrilled with the fact that "new scenes" of very old news have been released. But if anyone can whether a storm like this and come out stronger, it's definitely Kim. 
Your work paid off, baby girl. We're Team Kim 100 percent.
